üî¥ Deutsche Zeitformen (Zamanlar)
          A1 Pr√§sens (≈ûimdiki/Geni≈ü Zaman)
          A1 Perfekt  (Ge√ßmi≈ü - Konu≈üma dili) --> sein und haben
          A1 Pr√§teritum (Ge√ßmi≈ü - Yazƒ±lƒ±/Resmi dil) --> A1 seviyesinde sadece 2 tane fiili √∂ƒüren yeterli
             Konjunktiv 2 (Kapsamlƒ± bir konu ama A1de Sadece Rica formu √∂ƒüretilir. B1-B2 halen devam edersin)
          A1 Futur 1 (Gelecek Zaman)

        Pr√§sens                 (Present/Present Continuous/Future tense): 
                                Used to describe actions or events that are happening now or habitual actions.
                                        Ich spiele Tennis." (I am playing tennis.)

        Pr√§teritum              (Simple past tense): 
                                Generally used in written language and formal speech to describe completed actions in the past.
                                        "Ich spielte Tennis." (I played tennis.)
        Preteritum/Imperfekt    (Imperfect tense):
                                Similar to the simple past tense, it is used to describe actions in the past, but more commonly used in spoken language.
                                        "Ich spielte Tennis." (I played tennis.)

        Perfekt                 (Present perfect tense): 
                                Used to talk about completed actions in the past with a connection to the present.
                                        "Ich habe Tennis gespielt." (I have played tennis.)

        Plusquamperfekt         (Past perfect tense): 
                                Used to express actions that happened before another event in the past.
                                        "Ich hatte Tennis gespielt, als es zu regnen begann." (I had played tennis when it started to rain.)

        Futur I                 (Future tense): 
                                Used to express actions that will happen in the future.
                                        "Ich werde Tennis spielen." (I will play tennis.)

        Futur II                (Future II):
                                A compound tense used to express actions that will be completed in the future before another event takes place.
                                        "Ich werde Tennis gespielt haben, wenn du kommst."         (I will have played tennis by the time you come.)

        - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

        Pr√§sensprogressiv       (Present progressive): 
                                This is a compound tense used to express actions that are happening at the moment of speaking.
                                        "Ich bin am Tennis spielen." (I am playing tennis.)


        Konditional I           (Conditional I): 
                                A compound tense used to express hypothetical situations or polite requests.
                                        "Ich w√ºrde Tennis spielen." (I would play tennis.)

        Konditional II          (Conditional II): 
                                A compound tense used to express unreal or hypothetical situations in the past.
                                        "Ich w√ºrde Tennis gespielt haben, wenn es nicht geregnet h√§tte." (I would have played tennis if it hadn't rained.)

        Perfektprogressiv       (Present perfect progressive): 
                                A compound tense used to express ongoing actions that started in the past and are still continuing in the present.
                                        "Ich bin seit einer Stunde am Tennis spielen." (I have been playing tennis for an hour.)



